1
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,600
Propose?

2
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,200
Yes.

3
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,840
Peace

4
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,640
is getting married

5
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:45,920
-to Franc, Mom.
-Oh!

6
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,000
I thought you and…

7
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:50,480
Peace and I are just friends.

8
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:53,600
-Mr. Cent!
-Cent?

9
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,360
But now I know…

10
00:02:11,160 --> 00:02:12,880
The one who's really right for Peace

11
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,000
is Franc.

12
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,720
Sometimes the person we like

13
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,760
isn't the one meant for us.

14
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,640
But I think

15
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:32,160
someone who's right for you
will come along soon.

16
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,280
Will there really be someone
who's right for me?

17
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:52,160
Is this the right one, Mom? So quiet.

18
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,200
Yeah, she sent me the location.

19
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,200
This is it. It has to be the place.

20
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,200
Go bring the stuff for me, quickly!

21
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,600
Euang!

22
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,840
-Euang!
-Pim!

23
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:18,000
-Hey!
-Hey!

24
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,720
I've missed you!

25
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,000
I've missed you so much!

26
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,400
How have you been? Oh!

27
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,360
You look so much better. What did you do?

28
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,320
Really?

29
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:32,200
-Really.
-Nothing really. Just got richer,

30
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,240
so I look better.

31
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,600
Hey.

32
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:39,960
Pim, you're still as cute as ever.

33
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,240
Thank you, Euang.

34
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:44,520
Nick is waiting inside the house.
When I told him that you were coming,

35
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:47,040
-he got really excited!
-Really?

36
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,880
-Come on in.
-I've missed Nick. I brought lots of food.

37
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:51,720
-Really?
-Let's go!

38
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,080
Wait, Mom!

39
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,400
What about these?

40
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,800
Mom?

41
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:04,560
-You're all grown up now. Hello.
-Hello.

42
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,280
When he was a kid,
and I visited his house,

43
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,720
I saw him running around naked.

44
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:11,920
He still walks around naked in the house.

45
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,120
Huh?

46
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,560
-Really.
-Mom!

47
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,440
Is that normal?

48
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,519
Just kidding!

49
00:04:21,040 --> 00:04:23,080
You want to see, huh?
I know you want to see.

50
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,280
No way!

51
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:28,640
Let's stop teasing him.

52
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,520
Aunt Pim and Uncle Nick, they used to…

53
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,080
They were servers
at a Thai restaurant in LA,

54
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,320
where you were the chef.

55
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:37,520
I was three. Sometimes you'd take
me there, and they'd look after me.

56
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,920
You hadn't seen each other for a long time
until you reconnected on Facebook.

57
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,160
You told me everything along the way,
so now I remember.

58
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:52,760
Don't take it personally.
He's just very straightforward.

59
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,600
He really is. That's good.

60
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,400
-Better he talks than stays silent.
-Yeah.

61
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,840
Cent, what do you do for work now?

62
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:03,560
-I'm…
-Wait, don't! I'll answer for you.

63
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:06,440
If he starts, we won't finish all day.

64
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:10,480
He works in IT,
computers and stuff. That's it.

65
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,600
-Mom! That's not…
-Stop!

66
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,920
Just this much and she already gets it.
That's enough.

67
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:22,280
Forget about Cent's work.
Pim, Nick, what do you do now?

68
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:25,960
What do you do?

69
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:30,120
I'm going to water the plants.
Call me when it's dinner time.

70
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,800
Pim, what's up with Nick?

71
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,360
With a sigh that big,
it's going to be long.

72
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,520
Cent!

73
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:00,200
I'll just sit here and work.

74
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:02,640
Go ahead.

75
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:10,600
-Pim, tell me.
-Yes?

76
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,240
What's going on with Nick?

77
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:15,400
At first, the two of us
worked in advertising.

78
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,240
I handled the background work,
and Nick did the editing.

79
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,160
Back then, the business was booming.

80
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:23,880
Our combined salary per month
was over a hundred thousand.

81
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,040
But now,

82
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,880
the advertising industry has changed.

83
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:34,440
Nick just can't adapt.
He can't work with the younger team.

84
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:38,480
So it ended up like this.
Who would hire him?

85
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:46,200
In the end, he didn't do anything.
He just stayed in his office,

86
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:48,520
surrounded by his old collectibles,

87
00:06:49,040 --> 00:06:51,400
cameras, and film reels.

88
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:56,320
And he kept everything, refusing
to sell them, even when someone asked.

89
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:03,640
That's okay. What about you, Pim?
What are you doing now?

90
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:11,320
At first, I planned
to continue with advertising,

91
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,400
but the work got way more complicated.

92
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:17,360
Before, it was just print, radio, and TV.

93
00:07:17,440 --> 00:07:21,760
Now all these
new social media platforms exist.

94
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,600
So I decided to quit

95
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:28,840
and started making bags
to sell at craft markets.

96
00:07:28,920 --> 00:07:31,560
-Is that so? That's good.
-Yeah.

97
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:36,280
My daughter just graduated
and is looking for a job.

98
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,840
-Her name is…
-Fuang.

99
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,200
Her name is Fuang.

100
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,720
Her name is Fuang, really.

101
00:07:57,320 --> 00:08:00,160
-Remember the plan clearly.
-The music setup's ready, right?

102
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,880
-Okay, get into your positions.
-Today, I will prepare the stuff.

103
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,960
-She'll come in here. When she does,
-Once I do this,

104
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,600
-follow the plan exactly.
-start the next song.

105
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,880
-I'll signal for the next one.
-I think nothing will go wrong

106
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,560
if we follow this exactly.

107
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,560
-Actually, she's really sharp.
-The music…

108
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:15,440
Be careful. She'll notice
who's doing what.

109
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:19,240
People in this zone will stay there.
Servers will serve as assigned.

110
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:21,400
Stick to the plan. Be careful.

111
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:23,640
-Get into your positions.
-Be careful. She'll catch on to us.

112
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,160
Yuan!

113
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,840
-Everyone. Get into your positions.
-Okay, stick to the plan.

114
00:08:27,920 --> 00:08:29,440
-You go this way.
-Move, everyone!

115
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:31,480
Take your positions.

116
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,159
-Okay, just follow the plan.
-She's here!

117
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:34,960
Alright, everyone.

118
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,720
-Sit down. Quick, Pound.
-Ready?

119
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,159
I'm nervous.

120
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:42,039
She's probably almost here.

121
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:44,360
She's coming!

122
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,920
-Any moment now!
-Okay.

123
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,280
Call Peace and see where he is now.

124
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,720
-I'm nervous. Right?
-Me too.

125
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:33,040
She doesn't know about the proposal,
yet she's all dressed up.

126
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:35,120
If she knew, wouldn't she wear
an evening gown?

127
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,840
Stop teasing!

128
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:38,840
Hi.

129
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,120
Hey!

130
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:43,680
Sit here.

131
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,280
Come on.

132
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,520
Where's Fuang?

133
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,760
She went to answer a call. Her dad called.

134
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,120
Cute place.

135
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,440
Where are you now, Peace?

136
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,920
Franc is here.

137
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,800
I'm almost at the restaurant.

138
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,520
Fuang, here's the plan.

139
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:10,000
I'll enter through the back,
then wait by the fountain.

140
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:11,640
Cue the music.

141
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:13,480
The menu's here.

142
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:16,880
Take a look.

143
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,840
My favorite song!

144
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:50,480
What is it? Where are you taking me?

145
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,160
Where are you taking me?

146
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:54,360
-Go!
-Go with her!

147
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,280
Go!

148
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:57,920
Where are you taking me? Let's go.

149
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:00,000
Where are you taking me?

150
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,200
Follow her and take photos.

151
00:11:04,520 --> 00:11:06,440
Ask Peace where he is.

152
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,480
I'll go check on Peace outside.

153
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,840
Where's Peace?

154
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,840
I'll ask Fuang.

155
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:54,080
Pound!

156
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:55,880
Where the heck is Peace?

157
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:58,840
Peace is about to cross the street.
How is it over there?

158
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,120
-It really is a small world.
-Yeah.

159
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,440
Can't believe you know Fuang.

160
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,120
How did you even meet her?

161
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,440
Cent.

162
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,680
This brat. Why didn't you respond to him?

163
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,560
-He's always like this.
-It's okay.

164
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:11,800
What's up, Kenji?

165
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:24,960
Okay.

166
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,880
Hey, Franc!

167
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,520
-Franc!
-Franc!

168
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:52,800
-Franc!
-Franc!

169
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:55,600
-Yuan, Pound, take Franc to the sofa.
-I got this.

170
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,880
Alright.

171
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,920
-Watch out! Watch her head!
-Move aside!

172
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,160
Here's an inhaler.

173
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:05,920
Franc.

174
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,200
You're not going to work for me?

175
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:10,720
The person Ken found
just got hit by a car and died.

176
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,680
Finding someone new I can trust
will take time.

177
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:14,960
I can't wait. I have to get back to work.

178
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,760
I've already left things hanging too long.

179
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,560
Even here, you're still working.

180
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:20,840
Always on your computer.
You never pay attention to me.

181
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:21,840
Mom!

182
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,200
I do pay attention to you.

183
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,720
I take you to see your friends,
spend time with them.

184
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:27,680
I do it.

185
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,080
It's because I forced you
that you're doing it!

186
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,280
If I hadn't, you wouldn't have done it.

187
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:35,280
Mom, calm down. Wait!

188
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,800
Let's take it one step at a time.

189
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:39,400
About your day-to-day workers project,

190
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,120
I'll hire someone to do it!

191
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:45,400
There are tons
of skilled app developers now.

192
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:46,960
Even elementary school kids can do it.

193
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:50,040
I'll plan it and have someone else
implement it, okay?

194
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:51,840
Why aren't you doing it?

195
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,560
I don't have time, Mom.

196
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,360
Fine, then I won't return the shares.

197
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,440
-Mom!
-It's time for your medicine!

198
00:15:58,520 --> 00:15:59,480
-Not now, Pong!
-Go away, Pong!

199
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:12,320
Our agreement is that
you have to do this work yourself

200
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:14,240
for me to return the shares.

201
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:16,800
If you hire someone, you won't get them.

202
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,800
It doesn't matter who does it. Why me?

203
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,840
I want you here with me!

204
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,800
Mom.

205
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,680
I told you, if you really want to see me,

206
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:28,160
fly to Japan or Singapore.

207
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,840
I can send plane tickets every month,
even weekly if you want.

208
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,680
I can't go! I have to…

209
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:33,640
Why?

210
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,120
Other families do this too.

211
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:40,160
The parents live in another province,
and their kids work in Bangkok.

212
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:41,720
They only meet on holidays.

213
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,880
If they miss their kids,
they go visit them.

214
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,640
No one forces their kids like you do.

215
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:48,200
Geez! I've got my reasons.

216
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:53,320
And you said it yourself.
That app of yours doesn't take long.

217
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:56,000
Just finish it quickly.

218
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:59,400
I'm not asking for much time, Cent.

219
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:04,160
Once you're done, I'll return the shares.

220
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,079
That's it.

221
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:10,280
And the person Kenji recommended
is dead now.

222
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,440
You can find a new assistant.
It's not that hard.

223
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:20,400
Alright.

224
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,960
I'll find someone new to help

225
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:28,280
and finish your work as fast as possible.

226
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:35,640
But Mom, you don't have to do this.

227
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:39,480
If you really want to see me,
you can come whenever you want.

228
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:44,640
Whenever works for you, but not for me.

229
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,800
Today is more important than tomorrow.

230
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:54,040
I won't put my hopes on a future
that might never come.

231
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:11,480
Mom, are you really
not going to tell Cent?

232
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:17,880
There's no point. I know him well.

233
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,960
If he finds out,
he'll stress even more than I do.

234
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:25,560
In the end, I'd just have to comfort him.
It would stress me out.

235
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,880
Better not tell him. That's for the best.

236
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:38,440
And you, don't go blabbing.

237
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,400
Got it?

238
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,280
Yes, I understand.

239
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:19,200
MEDICAL OPINION CERTIFICATE

240
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,560
DIAGNOSED WITH STAGE THREE OVARIAN CANCER
UNDERWENT OVARY AND UTERUS SURGERY

241
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:27,680
<i>The biopsy results show cancer cells.</i>

242
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:31,800
<i>From here, we need to treat it</i>
<i>with chemotherapy as well.</i>

243
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,040
I have to do chemo,

244
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:37,440
right?

245
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:44,080
So removing my uterus and ovaries
didn't help at all?

246
00:19:45,360 --> 00:19:47,440
Some cancer cells
have spread to the lymph nodes.

247
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:51,800
Surgery alone cannot remove all of it.

248
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:55,760
Chemotherapy is needed
to prevent further spread and recurrence.

249
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,600
Am I going to die?

250
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:05,400
If treated according to protocol,
there's still a chance for recovery.

251
00:20:06,400 --> 00:20:09,680
<i>Let's discuss the details</i>
<i>and treatment steps.</i>

252
00:20:18,480 --> 00:20:22,280
<i>We just met. Aren't you going to ask</i>
<i>how I've been?</i>

253
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:24,680
-<i>You're already healthy.</i>
-<i>Nothing's guaranteed.</i>

254
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:29,080
<i>Whenever works for you, but not for me.</i>

255
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:33,120
<i>Today is more important than tomorrow.</i>

256
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:38,840
<i>I won't put my hopes on a future</i>
<i>that might never come.</i>

257
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:46,480
<i>Have you ever wondered</i>

258
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,680
<i>why we're alive?</i>

259
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,760
<i>I asked you this back when</i>
<i>we graduated high school.</i>

260
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,840
<i>You didn't think much then.</i>

261
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:01,800
<i>But I still believe…</i>

262
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:07,760
<i>we should give it some thought.</i>
<i>Time flies, and we've already graduated.</i>

263
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,680
<i>Maybe…</i>

264
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:17,400
-Life isn't as long as we think.
-True.

265
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:20,960
Life really is short. Look,

266
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:24,640
before we knew it, we've already
been in this world for over 20 years.

267
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,640
In no time, it'll be 30 or 40.

268
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,560
Exactly.

269
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:34,320
That's why we need to think
about why we're here.

270
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,520
If we do know, then what?

271
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:39,920
Once we know why we live,

272
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:45,960
our life has a purpose.
And once we have a purpose,

273
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:48,960
we must make it real.

274
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,800
When our time comes,

275
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:56,720
we won't regret the life we've lived.

276
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,480
Actually, we all have our things.

277
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,960
Fuang's selling her drawings.
I'm running my uncle's factory.

278
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,360
Bonus is waiting
for her teacher certification exam.

279
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:13,040
For that goal we think is right,

280
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,280
how do we really know it's the right one?

281
00:22:20,200 --> 00:22:22,400
I still wonder

282
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,280
if I even really want to be a teacher.

283
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,480
Have you ever questioned it too?

284
00:22:32,920 --> 00:22:36,240
No way am I going back
to my parents' canned fish factory.

285
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:41,120
But I don't know what I will do.

286
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,640
If Peace were still around,

287
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,040
he'd probably help me figure it out.

288
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:10,000
I'm sorry.

289
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:14,360
I know you're upset.

290
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,080
But we've been friends since kindergarten.

291
00:24:20,520 --> 00:24:22,520
We've always been open
with each other, right?

292
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:25,320
If you want to ask something, just ask.

293
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:32,840
There's something that's been bugging me.

294
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:38,360
I want to ask you directly,
so it's off my chest.

295
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:45,120
When you were dating Peace,

296
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:50,720
did you know Fuang liked him?

297
00:24:57,880 --> 00:25:00,440
Fuang liked Peace?

298
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:05,320
How long has she liked him?
How did you know?

299
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,600
And why didn't you tell me?

300
00:25:09,320 --> 00:25:10,480
Huh?

301
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,080
You really didn't know, did you?

302
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:19,920
How could I know? Fuang never told me.

303
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,560
Besides,

304
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:26,480
Peace was the one who asked me out.
That's why I became his girlfriend.

305
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:33,080
I'm not the type
to steal a friend's crush.

306
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:38,160
Fuang's my close friend.

307
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:41,040
If I had known,
I would've stayed away from him!

308
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:42,960
Okay!

309
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,720
I'm sorry for misunderstanding you.

310
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:59,320
It's good you asked me.
Now you don't have to guess.

311
00:26:02,880 --> 00:26:05,200
You said it yourself.

312
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:08,040
We've been friends since kindergarten.

313
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:13,360
You should know by now
I don't go after my friends' crushes!

314
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:52,400
My projects didn't get approved,
and no freelance work either.

315
00:26:56,320 --> 00:26:59,560
You're not planning to walk into the sea
and disappear, right?

316
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,880
I have a family to take care of.

317
00:27:08,920 --> 00:27:10,640
I wouldn't be so shallow.

318
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:17,040
-That's such a heroine's answer, right?
-A true heroine!

319
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,160
Seeing you laugh like this,

320
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:27,560
I feel relieved.

321
00:27:31,560 --> 00:27:36,400
I heard Bonus and Franc talking
about you and Peace.

322
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:44,560
Franc said she really didn't know
you had a crush on Peace.

323
00:27:46,120 --> 00:27:49,080
-So she…
-Hey, thanks for telling me.

324
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,160
But I'm not thinking about it anymore.

325
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:57,480
Peace isn't around now.

326
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,640
Let it just end.

327
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:02,640
Like I said,

328
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,760
we need to start doing something.

329
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,520
And I want

330
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:12,640
to see my parents live comfortably
before I die.

331
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:18,560
Nowadays, kids often die
before their parents.

332
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:24,760
True. Being just in our twenties

333
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:27,520
doesn't mean we'll outlive them.

334
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:33,040
You get it now, right? Why I've pushed
all that other stuff out of my head.

335
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,960
My life now

336
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:44,240
is just family, friends, and work.
That's enough.

337
00:28:49,040 --> 00:28:50,960
I talked to Mom.

338
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:53,760
She still won't cancel the project.

339
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,760
I need to find a new helper.

340
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:59,040
I'm planning to post it
with some headhunters too.

341
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:00,480
That's good, Cent.

342
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:04,000
If I can reach out to any other friends,
I'll let you know.

343
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,640
Thanks.

344
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,480
Hey.

345
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:10,760
About the new feature,
I want to test it for another day or two.

346
00:29:10,840 --> 00:29:12,960
I think it'll be ready to release soon.

347
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:15,600
<i>I'll update the clients right away.</i>

348
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:20,640
<i>Cent.</i>

349
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:23,600
I don't want to stress you out.

350
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:29,400
But it's not just your mom
who doesn't want to hold the shares.

351
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:33,480
I'm getting tired of this job.

352
00:29:34,320 --> 00:29:37,800
I want more time with my family.

353
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:40,480
-If someone offers a good price,
<i>-Whoa!</i>

354
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,760
I'd love to sell them.

355
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:45,360
Ken, hold on! Calm down.

356
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:49,760
You're selling because I came back
to work for my mom in Thailand?

357
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:51,880
No, Cent!

358
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,520
It's not about that.

359
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:57,720
I'm just tired of this job.

360
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:00,920
It is exhausting, Cent.

361
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:04,280
It's always a competition.

362
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:08,360
And now,

363
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:12,160
I've got a wife and kid.
I just can't keep up.

364
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:15,120
I really want to spend more time
with my family.

365
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:17,120
Hey, Ken!

366
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:19,880
Do you realize how hard it's been

367
00:30:19,960 --> 00:30:23,240
to build this? And you're selling
your shares that easily?

368
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:01,640
How about this, Ken?

369
00:31:02,720 --> 00:31:04,560
I'll head back to you right away.

370
00:31:04,640 --> 00:31:08,320
So you can be with your family.
I'll handle my mom.

371
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:09,600
<i>No!</i>

372
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:11,680
<i>You can't do that!</i>

373
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:14,280
<i>You have to finish your mom's project.</i>

374
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:17,760
<i>If I actually sell my shares,</i>

375
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:22,240
you'll still get her shares,
and you'll remain a major shareholder.

376
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:27,800
<i>I'm telling you this so you can prepare.</i>

377
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:32,440
<i>Secure your mom's shares</i>
<i>as fast as possible.</i>

378
00:31:33,200 --> 00:31:35,800
<i>Cent. Right now, for me,</i>

379
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:39,840
<i>time is more important than money.</i>

380
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:42,320
I've got enough money.

381
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:47,880
I really want to spend time
with my family now.

382
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:52,360
One day, if you have a partner and kids,

383
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:54,000
you'll understand.

384
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:58,120
Hold on, Rei!

385
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,760
<i>Daddy's here!</i>

386
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:07,360
Morning! Wake up!

387
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:09,760
-Pound, get up!
-Ouch!

388
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:11,480
Yuan, get up!

389
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,880
-Wake up!
-What the hell?

390
00:32:13,960 --> 00:32:15,640
Get up, Franc!

391
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:16,840
-Now!
-Ugh!

392
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,440
I'm going to make breakfast.

393
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:22,120
If you don't wake up and eat,
I'll feed it all to the dogs!

394
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:25,800
Hey, wake up! I know she means it!

395
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,920
Go take a shower now!

396
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:28,920
Can't I skip it?

397
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:30,560
No! Hurry up and wake everyone else.

398
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:31,960
Go shower already.

399
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:36,360
-I'm awake.
-Get up, Franc.

400
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:47,920
Hey, wake up!

401
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,200
Wake up! It's already afternoon!

402
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:33,600
Guys! Breakfast is ready!

403
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,720
-Go ahead.
-Let's eat!

404
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,760
-Dig in.
-Wow. Looks good!

405
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:39,800
-Yuan, you want some?
-Yeah.

406
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:41,920
Guys, take some photos.

407
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,760
-Wait.
-One, two.

408
00:33:45,720 --> 00:33:47,360
Alright.

409
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:48,760
-Is it good?
-Hey, Pound.

410
00:33:48,840 --> 00:33:51,280
I saw you pacing around the house
looking stressed.

411
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,200
Everything okay?

412
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:55,640
Not stressed, just a bit regretful.

413
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:59,480
This house cost my dad millions,
but we only come here a few times a year.

414
00:33:59,560 --> 00:34:01,520
We also have to pay high maintenance fees.

415
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:05,080
So I figured,
why not rent it out on Airbnb?

416
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:08,120
There are tons of vacation homes
around here.

417
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:10,000
I'm thinking of talking to the homeowners

418
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:11,760
and adding their places to the system.

419
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:14,000
Then I'll coordinate with the contractors,

420
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:16,440
have some renovations done,
and put them up for rent.

421
00:34:18,280 --> 00:34:19,679
Whoa, you sure think big!

422
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:21,480
-Yeah, true.
-Of course.

423
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:25,080
But you're rich.
You can do whatever you want.

424
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:26,320
-Yeah.
-You're Boss Pound.

425
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,560
Please take care of me.

426
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:29,679
It's called capitalizing.

427
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:33,120
Sure, my parents are rich,
but we've got to get even richer.

428
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:35,040
-Whoa.
-Like…

429
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,920
a "young billionaire" kind of thing.

430
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:38,520
You could say that.

431
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:46,400
Who's that?

432
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:49,920
It's my parents.
They're here to pick me up.

433
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:54,920
Today, I'm picking up my eldest daughter.

434
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,960
Hey, take it easy.

435
00:34:57,760 --> 00:35:00,360
Always filming and showing off
to your friends.

436
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:03,680
Hey! How many times do I have to tell you?

437
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:06,240
When I film, you stay quiet!

438
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:08,880
I have fans watching.

439
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:13,520
My friends don't go out much,
so whenever I go somewhere or eat,

440
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:16,480
I have to send them clips.

441
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:20,280
If I don't send them one day,
they'll ask for it. Just so you know!

442
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,480
Alright, suit yourself.

443
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:25,440
Let's keep going.

444
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:29,280
The atmosphere here is really nice.

445
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:31,200
Hello, Mom and Dad!

446
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,520
-Hey!
-Hello!

447
00:35:33,600 --> 00:35:35,520
-Mom!
-Oh, my dear.

448
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:38,160
-My poor baby.
-Was the trip tiring?

449
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,000
It's okay, dear.

450
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,520
No, don't make that face.

451
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:47,920
Long time no see. Hope you're both well.

452
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,560
We're fine.

453
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:52,560
In the blink of an eye,
everyone's already graduated.

454
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:53,960
Yes.

455
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:56,040
How about Friend? Almost graduated?

456
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,520
She's also almost done.

457
00:35:58,120 --> 00:35:59,880
She's busy with her thesis.

458
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:03,120
She asked me to invite everyone
to her graduation.

459
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:04,200
-Sure!
-Of course!

460
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:05,040
-Definitely!
-Yes!

461
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:05,920
I'll go take photos too.

462
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:07,520
Definitely going.

463
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:11,120
-Nice place, Pound. Right by the sea too.
-Thanks, Dad.

464
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:14,400
Mom, do you want to take a walk with Dad?
I'll pack my things first.

465
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:17,560
-Okay.
-Fuang, come along with me.

466
00:36:17,640 --> 00:36:19,280
-Sure.
-Let's go.

467
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:20,360
Give it a like too.

468
00:36:20,440 --> 00:36:21,720
-After you, Dad.
-Alright.

469
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,360
Actually, I have a business idea
about houses

470
00:36:24,440 --> 00:36:26,320
I'd like to get your advice on.

471
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:39,800
You didn't forget anything, right?

472
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:42,440
Let me check.

473
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,640
Nothing left.

474
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:51,560
Fuang.

475
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:02,560
I just found out about you and Peace.

476
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:07,280
I'm sorry.

477
00:37:14,560 --> 00:37:16,040
Don't worry about it.

478
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,520
It's not important.

479
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:23,560
And it's really nothing.

480
00:37:24,960 --> 00:37:28,640
You just need to know that he loves you

481
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:31,440
and you love him.

482
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:37,840
Franc.

483
00:37:44,560 --> 00:37:47,720
You're the one who's right for Peace.

484
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:02,520
Thanks so much.

485
00:38:06,120 --> 00:38:07,440
Thank you, Fuang.

486
00:38:11,480 --> 00:38:13,440
It's okay, you know.

487
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,200
Even without Peace,

488
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:21,520
you still have me and your friends.

489
00:38:33,360 --> 00:38:34,720
Hey.

490
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:37,720
Don't cry.

491
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,000
I'm trying to comfort you.

492
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:46,840
Don't get all sentimental like that, then.

493
00:38:50,160 --> 00:38:52,880
Stop, don't cry.

494
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,800
But still,

495
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,320
I want to apologize

496
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,600
for not telling you I was dating Peace.

497
00:39:07,640 --> 00:39:10,360
Back then, it was really complicated.

498
00:39:11,280 --> 00:39:12,120
You understand, right?

499
00:39:15,640 --> 00:39:17,120
You really understand, right?

500
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:22,680
I understand. It's okay, really.

501
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,520
But from now on,

502
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:31,040
if I like any guy,
you'll be the first to know!

503
00:39:37,680 --> 00:39:39,560
Why are you crying too?

504
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:41,440
Because you're crying!

505
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,840
Don't cry.

506
00:39:58,120 --> 00:39:59,760
Stop crying already.

507
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,360
I've stopped.

508
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:17,760
Mom, I can't come with you today.

509
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:20,800
I have an interview
to hire your project assistant.

510
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:22,400
I'll have Pong drive you.

511
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:28,120
Here she comes. I'll help.

512
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:32,080
Are you feeding
a whole village or something?

513
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:34,440
That mouth, who did you get it from?

514
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:35,600
Probably you, Mom.

515
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:37,320
It's obvious.

516
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,880
SOM TAM PALACE

517
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,040
Stay in the car.

518
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:49,840
I'll carry it myself.

519
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:52,440
Whoa, that's a lot! I can help.

520
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,760
I'm not that fragile.
Go back and watch the shop.

521
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:59,200
Okay.

522
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:30,480
Ma'am!

523
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,560
Are you okay?

524
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:38,760
<i>Your daughter sure is pretty.</i>
<i>Such a lovely face.</i>

525
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:42,120
<i>She's as pretty as I was when I was young.</i>
<i>Euang, don't you remember?</i>

526
00:41:42,200 --> 00:41:44,320
She takes after me more.

527
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:46,640
I take after both Mom and Dad.

528
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:49,400
Well said.

529
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:57,200
We've had Aunt Euang's meal,
now let's have some dessert.

530
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:01,360
Let's see. What did you bring?

531
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:05,320
I bought some Phetchaburi coconut custard

532
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:09,400
and Aunt Juea's mango sticky rice
from in front of the Hilton

533
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:13,040
and one from Aunt Nongnuch
across Chat Chai Market.

534
00:42:14,040 --> 00:42:15,200
Two places?

535
00:42:15,280 --> 00:42:18,160
Nick and I like different ones.

536
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:19,640
Fuang remembered.

537
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:22,160
Aunt Euang, please join us.

538
00:42:22,240 --> 00:42:24,680
Thank you. You've raised her well.

539
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:28,720
She's thoughtful and considerate.

540
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,840
And she remembers
what her parents like to eat.

541
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:33,560
She's also well-mannered and sweet.

542
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:39,240
Unlike my son!
He doesn't care about anyone at all.

543
00:42:39,320 --> 00:42:40,840
Don't even dream

544
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:43,280
he'd remember what I like.

545
00:42:44,880 --> 00:42:47,200
He doesn't even know what he likes.

546
00:42:47,920 --> 00:42:49,960
He spends all day
in front of his computer.

547
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:53,480
He doesn't have a girlfriend, either.

548
00:42:53,560 --> 00:42:54,800
He only has one friend.

549
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:58,360
His staff rarely go near him.
He's foul-mouthed!

550
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,400
Sharp-tongued, I mean.

551
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:06,280
I really worry about this son of mine.

552
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:26,240
ONLINE INTERVIEW

553
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:28,480
ONLINE INTERVIEW

554
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:38,840
<i>Fuang, Euang said her son knows you.</i>

555
00:43:39,840 --> 00:43:42,040
Knows me? How?

556
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:45,680
He saw you at Euang's som tam shop,

557
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:47,560
when you went to eat

558
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:49,120
with Peace.

559
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:54,960
He told me that you are

560
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:57,360
a junior of the man
he was going to work with.

561
00:43:57,440 --> 00:43:58,680
The one who just died.

562
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:03,720
Cent.

563
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:06,920
That's him. My son!

564
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:08,680
Yes, he really has a foul mouth.

565
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:11,960
-Fuang!
-Sorry.

566
00:44:12,040 --> 00:44:13,440
See?

567
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:16,360
You met him just once and already know
what kind of person he is.

568
00:44:16,440 --> 00:44:20,040
I don't know whether to be happy
or worried that he's so himself.

569
00:44:20,120 --> 00:44:22,120
But he seems sincere.

570
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:25,640
He's straightforward, says what he thinks.

571
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:27,080
It's good, no guessing needed.

572
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:35,520
You're the first one
to actually compliment Cent.

573
00:44:40,480 --> 00:44:43,840
Your mom said you just graduated
and are looking for a job, right?

574
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:45,560
Yes.

575
00:44:46,280 --> 00:44:47,840
Want to work with my son?

576
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:49,280
-Huh?
-Huh?

577
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:55,760
You want me to work for Cent?

578
00:44:56,800 --> 00:45:00,320
<i>This shirt is really cute!</i>
<i>Do you still have it in stock?</i>

579
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,160
Sorry!

580
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:09,560
I didn't mean to. I'm selling
stuff online at the same time.

581
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:11,600
<i>Go ahead with the interview.</i>

582
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:15,040
Please tell me about your work experience.

583
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:21,760
Wait a sec. By the way,
what position is this for?

584
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:26,080
<i>I'm not exactly sure about the position.</i>

585
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:29,080
Apparently, it's to help gather
information for an app.

586
00:45:31,080 --> 00:45:32,200
Yeah, for an app.

587
00:45:32,720 --> 00:45:34,600
An application?

588
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:37,240
Yes, an application!

589
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:39,920
Actually, it's my project,
but I hired him to do it.

590
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:42,440
But apps nowadays are so easy to make.

591
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:44,240
You don't even need an assistant.

592
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,000
-Even elementary kids--
-Can do it.

593
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:48,640
Right.

594
00:45:49,240 --> 00:45:51,880
What does Cent need an assistant for?

595
00:45:52,480 --> 00:45:54,880
I want someone who understands
Thai people, the Thai society,

596
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:57,120
and the basic issues affecting it.

597
00:45:57,200 --> 00:46:00,200
I graduated with a Bachelor's
and a Master's from the US.

598
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:04,480
<i>I think what I've done matches</i>
<i>the qualifications you're looking for.</i>

599
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:08,720
This project is directly related
to slums and the environment.

600
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:09,640
Stop!

601
00:46:30,160 --> 00:46:32,320
Sorry.

602
00:46:33,560 --> 00:46:35,480
You want me

603
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:38,840
to go get interviewed by him?

604
00:46:40,920 --> 00:46:43,920
Yes, and I'll tell him

605
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:47,200
that you're the most suitable.
He'll have to accept you.

606
00:46:52,600 --> 00:46:53,960
Euang.

607
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:58,720
Is this really a good idea?
Forcing him like that, it might not work.

608
00:46:58,800 --> 00:47:00,000
It's fine!

609
00:47:01,120 --> 00:47:04,240
This is my project.
Whatever I say, he has to follow.

610
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:10,760
Thank you, Aunt Euang,

611
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:13,400
for trusting me. But…

612
00:47:13,480 --> 00:47:15,120
I have work I want to do.

613
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:20,640
Even if it's still a work in progress,
I want to give it my all.

614
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:23,440
I want to make my dreams come true.

615
00:47:24,400 --> 00:47:27,800
And what is your dream, dear?

616
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:37,720
This is my dream.

617
00:47:40,040 --> 00:47:44,520
I love drawing, reading comics,
and all kinds of art.

618
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:48,200
I want to make art my career,

619
00:47:48,280 --> 00:47:49,600
not just a hobby.

620
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:56,640
You also made this.

621
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:01,640
I know

622
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:05,520
turning art into a career is hard.

623
00:48:06,640 --> 00:48:08,840
But I want to try anyway.

624
00:48:22,960 --> 00:48:23,960
How cute.

625
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:29,160
I want to support you.

626
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,160
Support me?

627
00:48:31,240 --> 00:48:34,520
Yes! Your work is beautiful.

628
00:48:34,600 --> 00:48:38,280
I don't know exactly how to support you.

629
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:40,560
I want your dream to come true.

630
00:48:41,840 --> 00:48:43,840
But can I ask you one thing?

631
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:46,320
What do you want me to do?

632
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:49,160
I want you to work with Cent.

633
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:51,360
What?

634
00:48:51,440 --> 00:48:54,840
Alright, let me put it simply.

635
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:58,440
I want you to do both things
at the same time.

636
00:48:58,520 --> 00:49:02,320
While you work with Cent,
you can also pursue your dream,

637
00:49:02,400 --> 00:49:04,600
drawing the art you love.

638
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:08,600
You can tell me how you want me
to support you or fund you.

639
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:10,080
Just let me know.

640
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:14,000
Do you want anything else?

641
00:49:16,960 --> 00:49:19,280
No, I don't want anything else.

642
00:49:19,360 --> 00:49:22,600
I mean…

643
00:49:23,280 --> 00:49:26,760
I'm speechless. I'm stunned, shocked,

644
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:28,440
and so happy!

645
00:49:29,600 --> 00:49:30,440
Thank you!

646
00:49:31,880 --> 00:49:35,400
But are you really sure

647
00:49:35,480 --> 00:49:37,600
he will accept me as his assistant?

648
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:38,880
<i>Fuang?</i>

649
00:49:38,960 --> 00:49:40,880
Fuang, your friend's daughter?

650
00:49:40,960 --> 00:49:44,000
Yes! I'm getting her to help you,

651
00:49:44,080 --> 00:49:45,560
and I'll fund her too.

652
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:48,640
You're getting her to help me?
Why didn't you ask me first?

653
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:51,640
No need to ask. It's an order!

654
00:49:51,720 --> 00:49:53,000
Dictator!

655
00:49:53,680 --> 00:49:55,880
I'm the major shareholder and your mom.

656
00:49:55,960 --> 00:49:57,320
Democracy isn't required here!

657
00:49:57,400 --> 00:50:00,080
Okay, she can help me.

658
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:01,800
But if she does a bad job,

659
00:50:01,880 --> 00:50:04,160
or your work gets delayed,
that's not my fault!

660
00:50:04,240 --> 00:50:07,200
I can read people well.
She can definitely help you.

661
00:50:07,920 --> 00:50:10,960
-What exactly are you funding her for?
-I don't know.

662
00:50:11,040 --> 00:50:14,200
You're funding her without knowing?
Has she brainwashed you?

663
00:50:14,280 --> 00:50:15,520
No way!

664
00:50:15,600 --> 00:50:18,600
If you want to know what she can do,
talk to her yourself.

665
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:21,320
I'll have her present her work to you.

666
00:50:21,400 --> 00:50:24,280
You help me figure out
what I should invest in.

667
00:50:24,360 --> 00:50:25,600
Alright, I'll call to set it up.

668
00:50:25,680 --> 00:50:30,080
Wait! Mom. Calm down, girlie.

669
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:32,160
I can barely handle my own work.

670
00:50:32,240 --> 00:50:34,160
How am I supposed
to listen to someone present?

671
00:50:34,240 --> 00:50:36,280
I'm not doing it. No way!

672
00:50:36,360 --> 00:50:39,800
And the shares, do you want them or not?

673
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:41,480
Just listen to her for a few minutes.

674
00:50:41,560 --> 00:50:43,440
You're acting like
it's the end of the world.

675
00:50:43,520 --> 00:50:46,280
If seven years ago I hadn't endured
listening to your presentation,

676
00:50:46,360 --> 00:50:49,720
you might not have
what you have today, Cent!

677
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:51,680
Learn to give to others sometimes.

678
00:50:51,760 --> 00:50:55,680
Eight minutes! I'm giving her
only eight minutes to present her idea.

679
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:57,800
See you the day after tomorrow.
Go grab a drink!

680
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:01,760
Okay.

681
00:51:03,880 --> 00:51:06,360
I'll prepare as best I can.

682
00:51:06,440 --> 00:51:10,320
Thank you so much, Aunt Euang.
See you soon.

683
00:51:16,400 --> 00:51:21,040
<i>Eight-minute presentation.</i>
<i>What am I supposed to present?</i>

684
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:27,160
Franc, may I come in?

685
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:33,120
Someone just delivered something.

686
00:51:33,800 --> 00:51:36,400
-It might be…
-Yeah.

687
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:37,520
I know.

688
00:51:38,600 --> 00:51:40,440
Peace's mom just called and told me.

689
00:51:45,120 --> 00:51:46,800
Are you okay, Franc?

690
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:04,560
Franc, where did these photos come from?

691
00:52:05,680 --> 00:52:07,320
They're from…

692
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:12,440
the day Peace set up the proposal.

693
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:15,680
Aw, dear.

694
00:52:50,760 --> 00:52:51,880
Whoa, Franc!

695
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:54,960
Franc!

696
00:52:59,320 --> 00:53:00,520
It's okay, dear.

697
00:53:02,120 --> 00:53:03,840
I miss him.

698
00:53:06,360 --> 00:53:08,240
I miss him.

699
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:12,920
SOM TAM PALACE

700
00:53:19,240 --> 00:53:22,240
Have a motorbike taxi deliver these
to Uncle Nick and Aunt Pim for me.

701
00:53:23,560 --> 00:53:24,520
All of this?

702
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:27,240
Yes, all of it.

703
00:53:28,640 --> 00:53:30,560
Enter the code yourself.

704
00:53:32,360 --> 00:53:35,200
That family mostly eats vegetables.

705
00:53:36,440 --> 00:53:38,840
Uncle Nick and Aunt Pim are really nice.

706
00:53:38,920 --> 00:53:40,440
They used to help me a lot.

707
00:53:41,360 --> 00:53:43,800
Now they're struggling, so I want to help.

708
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:47,400
Fuang is also sweet and lovely,

709
00:53:48,000 --> 00:53:50,200
well-mannered, and kind-hearted.

710
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:54,400
Stop staring already.

711
00:53:54,480 --> 00:53:57,080
Call a bike now. The food's getting cold!

712
00:54:00,120 --> 00:54:01,880
-I'll deliver it myself.
-Huh?

713
00:54:02,560 --> 00:54:03,840
Did I hear that right?

714
00:54:04,440 --> 00:54:06,160
You're going to deliver the food for me?

715
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:09,000
Oh my, Thailand! Snow might start falling!

716
00:54:10,920 --> 00:54:11,920
Wait.

717
00:54:14,240 --> 00:54:17,720
Tell me honestly,
why do you want to go to their house?

718
00:54:22,640 --> 00:54:23,720
You want to see some old films?

719
00:54:24,480 --> 00:54:25,480
Yes.

720
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:28,040
I've never seen 16mm films before.

721
00:54:28,560 --> 00:54:29,760
Can I take a look?

722
00:54:33,880 --> 00:54:35,640
Of course. Come inside.

723
00:54:40,760 --> 00:54:43,040
Sometimes, even money
can't buy things like this.

724
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:47,440
I think film has a charm
that digital can't replace.

725
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:51,480
Look at film cameras.
They've come back into style.

726
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:54,920
Sometimes people
just crave simple, classic things.

727
00:55:05,840 --> 00:55:10,040
Hollywood directors like Nolan or Quentin
still insist on shooting on film only.

728
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:20,160
Can I hold it?

729
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:23,040
-Sure.
-Thank you.

730
00:55:40,600 --> 00:55:41,880
Who knows, Uncle Nick.

731
00:55:42,840 --> 00:55:45,640
Someday the stuff in this room
could be priceless,

732
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:48,360
at least sentimentally.

733
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:00,120
Thank you.

734
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:02,880
Thank you so much.

735
00:56:02,960 --> 00:56:04,880
Even though you're from
the new generation,

736
00:56:05,840 --> 00:56:08,680
a kid of the digital age,
who works with computers,

737
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:11,240
you still see the value in old films.

738
00:56:11,960 --> 00:56:12,960
I really appreciate it.

739
00:56:15,120 --> 00:56:16,040
You're welcome.

740
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:25,520
What are you doing, Dad?

741
00:56:32,240 --> 00:56:33,080
Cent!

742
00:56:33,160 --> 00:56:36,280
Every Facebook page posted news about you.

743
00:56:36,360 --> 00:56:38,280
It is even trending on Twitter!

744
00:56:38,800 --> 00:56:40,680
#NoGoodbye.

745
00:56:40,760 --> 00:56:42,400
Thank you for the compliment!

746
00:56:45,080 --> 00:56:46,720
I mean, for saying
my drawing is beautiful.

747
00:56:47,560 --> 00:56:49,320
Thank you. Really, thank you!

748
00:56:49,400 --> 00:56:51,000
You're making the app
in exchange for shares.

749
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:55,200
And you'll help her
with her project as my son.

750
00:56:55,280 --> 00:56:59,040
-Mom!
-Hey, listen!

751
00:57:00,120 --> 00:57:02,240
Thank you, my dear son.

752
00:57:45,400 --> 00:57:50,360
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
